# Cursor / GitHub Copilot — Project Rules for MAMS

You are working on the Makson Attendance Management System (MAMS). This is a compliance-critical
on-prem MERN application for an Indian pharmaceutical manufacturer. Generic Express/React patterns
will fail review here — read the rules below carefully.

## ARCHITECTURAL CONSTANTS

- Stack: MongoDB 7 + Express + Mongoose + TypeScript (strict) + React + Vite + Node 22
- Monorepo: mams-server, mams-web, mams-shared
- Timezone: Asia/Kolkata everywhere (store UTC, display IST, use date-fns-tz)
- Auth: JWT with bcrypt(12) password hashing, 8h access token + 30d refresh
- Deployment: Makson on-prem server (no cloud services at runtime — no S3, no Cloudinary, no SaaS)
- Internal comms: Microsoft Teams (no Slack)

## COMPLIANCE CONSTRAINTS — DO NOT VIOLATE

### Hours are source of truth, not days
- Standard divisor: 9.5 hrs/day
- equivalentDays = compliantHours / 9.5 (computed at query time, never stored)
- Never let day-based logic drive a calculation

### Original biometric records are immutable
- Mongoose schemas for RawPunch and Attendance must NOT expose updateOne, deleteOne, findOneAndUpdate, or findOneAndDelete
- Corrections create new AttendanceCorrection records that reference (do not mutate) the original
- If user asks to "fix" or "edit" a punch, build it as a new correction, not a mutation

### Sensitive fields masked by default
Fields: aadhaar, pan, bankAccount, ifsc, pfNumber, esiNumber
- Mask format: keep last 4 chars, replace rest with X
- Centralised middleware at response-serialisation layer — impossible to bypass per-route
- Unmasking gated on: authorised role + explicit user action + audit-log row written BEFORE plaintext returned (atomic)
- NEVER write console.log(employee), console.log(attendance), console.log(req.body) — leaks unmasked PII
- Aadhaar typed manually by HR; no OCR, no UIDAI API, no checksum validation in Phase 1

### Smart Anchor v2 is deterministic
- Same (employeeId, YYYY-MM-DD, rawPunch) -> same compliantPunch, FOREVER, across processes/restarts/deployments
- Park-Miller LCG seeded by hash of employeeId + ':' + 'YYYY-MM-DD'
- NEVER use Math.random(), Date.now(), crypto.randomBytes() in Smart Anchor or PRNG code paths
- Property-based test (fast-check) is mandatory — 1000 random pairs, run twice, assert identical sequences

### Dual-credential view at query layer
- ONE attendance table
- Auth middleware tags req.user.viewMode = 'real' | 'compliant'
- Same UI, same endpoints, different payload based on viewMode
- Two seed users: hr.admin (real), hr.compliance (compliant)

### No deemed acceptance
- Every milestone needs explicit written sign-off
- No time-based auto-approval ANYWHERE in the system (e.g., adjustments don't auto-approve after N days)

### Visual spec is locked
- Mockup: https://makson-payroll-mockup.netlify.app
- Approved 30 Apr 2026
- Any UI deviation = Change Request (don't suggest visual variations during implementation)

## CODING RULES

- Default: write NO comments. Only when the WHY is non-obvious.
- No fallbacks, retries, validation for impossible scenarios. Trust framework guarantees.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Don't add features beyond the task's acceptance criteria.
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no implicit return types on exported functions.

## TESTS REQUIRED

- Compliance-critical paths use fast-check property-based tests, not just example tests:
  - Smart Anchor determinism (1000 random pairs, run twice, identical)
  - Masking no-leakage (1000 random objects, no sensitive-digit run in JSON output)
- Every endpoint touching sensitive data asserts AuditLog.count() incremented in test setup
- CI must pass before merge

## OUT OF SCOPE — DO NOT IMPLEMENT EVEN IF SUGGESTED

- Aadhaar UIDAI checksum/format validation
- Letterhead PDF with compliance header (only plain print-to-PDF in Phase 1)
- DD/MM/YYYY date standardisation across exports (Phase 2)
- In-app brand asset upload UI (deployment-time config only)
- Payroll, PF/ESI/PT returns, TDS, Form 16
- Leave management
- Mobile apps
- SMS/WhatsApp/email notifications
- Multi-language UI
- Cloud services at runtime (S3, Cloudinary, Auth0, etc.)
